# Delegating via PLX-MC MCP

Prefer the **PLX-MC** MCP server for task lifecycle + optional swarm delegation.

## Tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `mc_checkout_task` | Mint checkout + `MC-Checkout` PR stamp |
| `mc_report_progress` | Stage/notes updates |
| `mc_complete_task` | Done marker + evidence |
| `mc_search_tasks` / `mc_get_context` | Discovery |
| `dispatch_to_swarm` | COS orchestration (requires `SWARM_DISPATCH_ENABLED=1`) |

## Default state

Ships **disabled** (`PLX_MC_MCP_ENABLED=0` in committed `.cursor/mcp.json`). Linux/macOS use
`tools/plx-mc-mcp/launch.mjs` (AWS key fallback). Windows: run
`python scripts/bootstrap-windows-secrets.py`, then point the local MCP block at
`scripts/run-plx-mc-mcp.ps1` (see runbook). Team MCP: set `PLX_MC_MCP_ENABLED=1` in the console.

